  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Low Fire Gloss', 'LG-65', 'Amber', 'Cone 05', 'Amber is a brilliant, glossy, semi- transparent light brown glaze with dark brown specks that breaks clear over textured surfaces.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Low Fire Gloss', 'LG-67', 'Fire Orange', 'Cone 05', 'Fire Orange is a brilliant, glossy, semi- transparent deep tangerine glaze that breaks clear over textured surfaces'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Low Fire Gloss', 'LG-68', 'Vivid Orange', 'Cone 05', 'Vivid Orange is a brilliant, glossy, semi- transparent cheddar orange glaze that breaks clear over textured surfaces.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Low Fire Gloss', 'LG-760', 'Pale Yellow', 'Cone 05', 'Pale Yellow is a brilliant, glossy, semi- transparent flaxen yellow glaze that breaks clear over textured surfaces.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Low Fire Matte', 'LM-10', 'Transparent Matte', 'Cone 05', 'Transparent Matte is a satin glaze that works well with surface decoration. If you spend all that time painting with Velvet Underglaze, make sure you use this to reduce the glare of a glossy glaze. Works great with any AMACO underglaze product. Apply thin over texture and surface decorations to prevent pooling. This glaze can become semi-opaque when it is thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Low Fire Matte', 'LM-11', 'Opaque White', 'Cone 05', 'Opaque White is a soft, matte bright white glaze that offers a unique, satin surface and will not flow during firing.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-02', 'Black Tulip', 'Cone 05', 'Black Tulip is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a greenish obsidian where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-10', 'Transparent Pearl', 'Cone 05', 'Transparent Pearl is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft, milky white where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-11', 'White Clover', 'Cone 05', 'White Clover is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a lovely light white where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-12', 'Tawny', 'Cone 05', 'Tawny is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft, sandy yellow where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-20', 'Bluebell', 'Cone 05', 'Bluebell is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft, powdery blue where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-21', 'Aquamarine', 'Cone 05', 'Aquamarine is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a rich, saturated teal where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-23', 'Sapphire Blue', 'Cone 05', 'Sapphire Blue is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a rich electric blue where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-26', 'Turquoise', 'Cone 05', 'Turquoise is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft cerulean where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-30', 'Autumn Leaf', 'Cone 05', 'Autumn Leaf is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft, pale yellow where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-42', 'Moss Green', 'Cone 05', 'Moss Green is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft, mint green where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-52', 'Fuchsia', 'Cone 05', 'Fuchsia is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a bright cherry-blossom pink where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-54', 'Dusty Rose', 'Cone 05', 'Dusty Rose is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a soft, milky pink where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Opalescent', 'O-57', 'Mottled Burgundy', 'Cone 05', 'Mottled Burgundy is an active, flowing low-fire glaze that breaks clear over texture and pools a rich, deep aubergine where thick. Because of its tendency to break and expose the clay body beneath, this glaze looks stunning over 67-M (Sedona) and over textured ware that has been painted with underglaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Phase Glaze', 'PG-24', 'Night Rain', 'Cone 5/6', 'A deep indigo blue with lighter blue visual texture, PG-24 Night Rain is reminiscent of a night sky through a rain spattered window. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. For layering, please apply 2 coats over 2 coats. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3-4 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.)'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Phase Glaze', 'PG-42', 'Teal Drift', 'Cone 5/6', 'A vivid turquoise with a subtle spots where thick, PG-42 Teal Drift is a rich, tropical color. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. For layering, please apply 2 coats over 2 coats. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3-4 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.)'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Phase Glaze', 'PG-54', 'Lunar Pink', 'Cone 5/6', 'A pale, cool pink with white visual texture where thick. PG-54 Lunar Pink gives the visual effect of sunlight scattering through the Earth''s atmosphere during the moonrise. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. For layering, please apply 2 coats over 2 coats. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3-4 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.)'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Phase Glaze', 'PG-55', 'Floating Lavender', 'Cone 5/6', 'A light purple with lighter visual spot texture where thick, PG-55 Floating Lavender is light and airy as a cloud at sunset. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. For layering, please apply 2 coats over 2 coats. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3-4 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.)'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-01', 'Saturation Metallic', 'Cone 5/6', 'Great for sculptural work and industrial ware, Saturation Metallic is a satin metallic black glaze that resembles steel and other metals. Saturation Metallic is great as an accent glaze. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze. WARNING: This product can expose you to chemicals including Lithium carbonate, which are known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm. For more information go to www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-02', 'Saturation Gold', 'Cone 5/6', 'Saturation Gold has a smooth, satin/matte finish that is a dark gold similar to bronze when fired. Perfect for sculptural work and industrial ware, this glaze could be a unique accent for any work of art. Saturation Gold requires a heavy application to develop its gold metallic finish. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-04', 'Palladium', 'Cone 5/6', 'This unique metallic glaze has a mirrorlike finish when fired and adds beautiful, shimmering accents to any work. Because it is not food safe, this glaze is perfect for sculptural work that calls for reflective, glassy surfaces. Palladium requires 3 coats to develop the smooth mirror finish. This glaze is fluid so be careful not to overfire. This glaze likes low porosity bodies. It is also great as an accent glaze or for layering with other AMACO glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-09', 'Vintage Gold', 'Cone 5/6', 'Vintage Gold is a glossy metallic glaze which develops small triangular gold crystals with dark haloes like a glittering patina. This opaque glaze does not break over texture. For best results apply three even brush coats. ​A dramatic glaze for sculptural or non-functional work. Glaze may run.​ Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-10', 'June Bug', 'Cone 5/6', 'June Bug is a glossy, dark green metallic glaze that develops small triangular iridescent crystals, like the wings of a beetle. This opaque glaze does not break over texture.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-11', 'Blue Spark', 'Cone 5/6', 'Blue Spark is a glossy, royal blue glaze which develops small triangular dark gray metallic crystals that make this glaze look like lapis lazuli. This opaque glaze does not break over texture. For best results apply three even brush coats. Glaze may run. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-12', 'Blue Midnight', 'Cone 5/6', 'Blue Midnight is a glossy black glaze that breaks into blue highlights where thick. This glaze is good for textured work and also layers well with other Potter''s Choice Glazes. Blue Midnight benefits from a heavy application - it creates more separation from the base glaze to the float. Texture accentuates this effect. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-13', 'Serpentine Green', 'Cone 5/6', 'This glaze is currently available at your local distributor. Find a distributor near you HERE . PC-13 Serpentine Green is a semi-matte soft green glaze that breaks light blue over texture. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-14', 'Lapis Flow', 'Cone 5/6', 'This glaze is currently available at your local distributor. Find a distributor near you HERE . Lapis Flow is a flowy glaze, varying in color from soft blue to purple and breaking green over texture. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-15', 'Satin Oribe', 'Cone 5/6', 'A modern take on a traditional Japanese oribe glaze, Satin Oribe adds a wonderful blue-green burnished look to your wares. Over texture, the dark green pools and light grey breaks bring an extra level of depth to this opaque glaze. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-16', 'Purple Crystal', 'Cone 5/6', 'Purple Crystal is a matte violet glaze for Cone 5 that becomes glossy deep indigo with purple crystal floats at Cone 6. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-17', 'Honey Flux', 'Cone 5/6', 'Honey Flux is a creamy color that increases flow when layered over glazes. Opaque honey and cream at Cone 5 that shifts to a beautiful fluid white with honey flecks at Cone 6.​ Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-18', 'Tuscan Blue', 'Cone 5/6', 'This glaze is currently available at your local distributor. Find a distributor near you HERE . PC-18 Tuscan Blue is a deep blue, semi-matte glaze that breaks light blue to moss green over texture. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-19', 'Moon River', 'Cone 5/6', 'This glaze is currently available at your local distributor. Find a distributor near you HERE . PC-19 Moon River is a dreamy, flowy glaze shifting in color from a soft periwinkle to a milky blue. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-20', 'Blue Rutile', 'Cone 5/6', 'Great for layering and textured work, Blue Rutile is an active, complex glaze that is a flowing light blue where thick and breaks brown where thinner. Great for layering and always interesting, this glaze is always one of our top selling Potters Choice glazes! A very fluid glaze. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-21', 'Arctic Blue', 'Cone 5/6', 'Arctic Blue is a beautiful, opaque light blue that has a smooth, consistent surface and breaks tan over texture. This glaze lends very well to layering with other Potter''s Choice Glazes. Arctic Blue benefits from a heavy application. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-22', 'Blue Stone', 'Cone 5/6', 'Similar in texture to a worn stone found at the bottom of a river, Blue Stone carries a softness that is visible in its smooth blue-green matte color. The different shades of green feather into dark blues when applied over texture wares. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-23', 'Indigo Float', 'Cone 5/6', 'Indigo Float is an intensely blue glaze with a lighter blue surface float. This rich cobalt glaze breaks deep blue where thinner. Great for layering with other potters choice glazes! Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-24', 'Sapphire Float', 'Cone 5/6', 'Sapphire Float is a glossy, denim-blue glaze with a wispy white rutile float, that breaks a green-gray color over texture. The rutile float dramatically flows with texture and forms beautiful naturally flowing patterns. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-25', 'Textured Turquoise', 'Cone 5/6', 'A subtle turquoise gloss, green-beige where thin, but a beautiful aqua where thick. Great for textured ware and layering with other Potter''s Choice glazes. It is a fluid glaze. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-26', 'Blue Lagoon', 'Cone 5/6', 'The cool tones of Blue Lagoon break milky green and pool into light blue shallows when applied over deep texture. When heavier coats are applied this allows the glaze to float up and create interesting surface variations similar to tides in a blue lagoon. A fluid glaze. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-27', 'Tourmaline', 'Cone 5/6', 'Tourmaline is an intense, opaque blue-green glaze that forms a smooth, strong surface. Goes well layered with other potters choice glazes! Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-28', 'Frosted Turquoise', 'Cone 5/6', 'Frosted Turquoise is an opaque gray-blue glaze that appears to crackle over deep blue but has a smooth, satiny surface. This glaze is a great, detailed surface decoration for subtle, simple forms. Frosted Turquoise benefits from a heavy application to achieve its color breaking effect. The glaze color is susceptible to variation due to iron fuming from nearby pots in firing. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-29', 'Deep Olive Speckle', 'Cone 5/6', 'Deep Olive Speckle is a rich, translucent, glossy green glaze with darker green speckles. Looks great when layered with our other Potter''s Choice glazes. This glaze contains black speckles that may clog a spray gun. Make sure glaze is well-mixed for even distribution of speckles. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-30', 'Temmoku', 'Cone 5/6', 'Temmoku is a textured, satin-matte dark brown/tan speckled glaze that looks great layered beneath some of the more fluid Potter''s Choice glazes. With its consistent surface and reliable results, this glaze makes a fantastic liner for cups, pots, bowls, and other ware. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-31', 'Oatmeal', 'Cone 5/6', 'Oatmeal is a toasty, light beige glaze that is relatively translucent and breaks clear over textured surfaces. This glaze is great for layering with other Potters Choice glazes. Try layered over PC-33 Iron Lustre! Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-32', 'Albany Slip Brown', 'Cone 5/6', 'Like the traditional potter''s glaze that inspired it, Albany Slip Brown is fluid and butter colored where thick and russet where thin. Great layered over or under other Potter''s Choice glazes. WARNING: This product can expose you to chemicals including Lithium carbonate, which are known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm. For more information go to www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-33', 'Iron Lustre', 'Cone 5/6', 'More restrained, but similar to a regular blue glaze, Iron Lustre is brown where thin with blue-gray floats where thick. It is beautiful on texture and layers well with other Potter''s Choice glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-34', 'Light Sepia', 'Cone 5/6', 'Light Sepia is an opalescent grey glaze that features strong variations on textured ware. This glaze breaks golden beige where thin and lends well to layering with our other Potters Choice Glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-36', 'Ironstone', 'Cone 5/6', 'Ironstone is a glossy, dark glaze that is a deep chocolatey brown where thin with a beige-bronze float where thicker. Mixes well with other Potter''s Choice Glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-38', 'Iron Yellow', 'Cone 5/6', 'Iron Yellow is a glossy, soft yellow glaze with flecks of iron, that is relatively opaque and breaks clear over texture. Excellent as a liner glaze for pots where the goal is to show off the decorations on the outside of the vessel. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-40', 'True Celadon', 'Cone 5/6', 'True Celadon is a delicate light green glaze that reproduces the effects of traditional Asian celadons. This glaze looks striking over any textured ware and has great color response when layered with our other Potter''s Choice glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-41', 'Vert Lustre', 'Cone 5/6', 'Vert Lustre is a beautiful flowing green glaze with a metallic sheen like that of ancient Persian Lusterware. This glaze reacts well to texture and has great effects when layered with other Potter''s Choice Glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-42', 'Seaweed', 'Cone 5/6', 'Seaweed is a fluid, deep green glaze that layers beautifully with a variety of Potter''s Choice glazes. This glaze breaks brownish over texture and becomes more fluid with thickness. Pay attention to application thickness so the glaze does not flow onto kiln shelves during firing. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-43', 'Toasted Sage', 'Cone 5/6', 'Toasted Sage is an opaque, warm gray glaze that has subtle, frothy tones of pink and green. This glaze layers very well with other Potter''s Choice glazes- particularly as a top coat.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-44', 'Sage', 'Cone 5/6', 'Sage is an opaque, warm gray green glaze. This glaze layers very well with other Potter''s Choice glazes- particularly as a top coat. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-45', 'Dark Green', 'Cone 5/6', 'Dark green is a fluid, translucent emerald glaze that shows off textured and carved ware. Use over a wash of our High Fired Texturizer for added definition. Layers well with our other Potter''s Choice glazes! Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-46', 'Lustrous Jade', 'Cone 5/6', 'Lustrous jade is a glossy, opaque glaze that boasts a soft, even green finish like the gemstone it is named for. This glaze layers well with our other Potter''s Choice glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-47', 'Emerald Falls', 'Cone 5/6', 'Emerald Falls is a beautiful glossy green glaze that breaks lighter and pools into a mauve grey-green. When heavier coats are applied this allows the glaze to float up and create interesting surface variations echoing mossy patches found in rolling emerald landscapes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-48', 'Art Deco Green', 'Cone 5/6', 'Art Deco Green is a glossy, light blue-green glaze that floats metallic spots to the surface resembling a patinate copper roof. Clay body and application can affect the size and abundance of the metallic spots.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-49', 'Frosted Melon', 'Cone 5/6', 'Frosted Melon is a very unique glaze with some qualities that can be exploited for additional interest. It has a massive, beige float with heavy application. This float "cracks", showing the green of the glaze below while still maintaining a smooth, satin surface. This subtle glaze is beautiful on smooth and textured ware alike.The glaze color is susceptible to variation due to iron fuming from other pots nearby in firing. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-52', 'Deep Sienna Speckle', 'Cone 5/6', 'Deep Sienna Speckle is a warm, rich russet glaze that is translucent with dark speckles that resemble the surface of reduction stoneware glazes. For more depth and concentration of color, apply thicker. This glaze layers well with our other Potter''s Choice glazes. This glaze contains black speckles, so make sure glaze is mixed well to assure they are well dispersed. Specks may clog spray gun. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-53', 'Ancient Jasper', 'Cone 5/6', 'Ancient Jasper is a fluid, opaque glaze that transitions from soft black to olive green to rust red as it is applied thicker. This glaze has an active, varied surface by itself and layers with our other Potter''s Choice glazes with striking results. Ancient Jasper benefits from a heavier application. This glaze will produce reds on all clay bodies, although iron-bearing clay bodies will produce the widest range of colors. No special cooling cycles or soaks are needed. Soaking can actually diminish the reds. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-55', 'Chun Plum', 'Cone 5/6', 'Chun Plum is a pink-red translucent glaze that breaks light tan over textures. This glaze imitates the copper reds of Asia but with a reliable color response in oxidation firings. Layer over other Potters Choice glazes for a warmer tone and hints of pink and red. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-56', 'Ancient Copper', 'Cone 5/6', 'Inspired by classic tomato red reduction glazes, Ancient Copper is an iridescent, iron red glaze that breaks dark brown over texture and pools dark yellow-green, giving it a weathered appearance. Ancient Copper is a satin at cone 5, and more glossy with metallic floats at cone 6. Avoid slow-cooling cycles when firing.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-57', 'Smokey Merlot', 'Cone 5/6', 'Smokey Merlot is a warm, dark purple glaze with a soft float of lilac over the surface. This glaze looks stunning on smooth surfaces, over textured surfaces, and layered with our other Potters Choice glazes. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-59', 'Deep Firebrick', 'Cone 5/6', 'Deep Firebrick is an opaque, speckled brick red glaze that breaks translucent where thin. This bold, dark red glaze has a strong presence and layers well under or over other Potter''s Choice glazes. This glaze contains black specks that may clog spray guns. Make sure glaze is well-mixed to ensure even distribution of speckles. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-61', 'Textured Amber', 'Cone 5/6', 'Textured Amber is a semi-matte brown glaze that has a varied, translucent surface with a textured float of opaque tan speckles. Try layering this glaze with our other Potter''s Choice glazes! Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-62', 'Textured Amber Brown', 'Cone 5/6', 'Textured Amber Brown is a glossy brown glaze that breaks lighter where thinner like a traditional temmoku glaze. This glaze layers well with our other Potter''s Choice glazes and produces fluid, beautiful effects.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-63', 'Cosmic Tea Dust', 'Cone 5/6', 'Cosmic Tea Dust is a sparkly, dark brown glaze, which breaks a light yellow-brown over texture. The sparkle shifts subtly from silver to copper to give the glaze an iridescent quality. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-64', 'Aventurine', 'Cone 5/6', 'Aventurine is an amber glaze with crystal flecks, that breaks golden over texture and pools a darker shade in recessed areas. This glaze is fluid so leave room for vertical flow. Testing is recommended to find the proper application and firing. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes. *Note that all dry dipping glazes can be difficult to layer. Dipping glazes behave differently from brushing and they require thorough testing prior to layering full piece.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-65', 'Black Aventurine', 'Cone 5/6', 'Black Aventurine is a fluid, rich black glaze that develops a metallic sparkle.​ If slow cooled, this glaze will grow crystals. WARNING: This product can expose you to chemicals including Lithium carbonate, which are known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm. For more information go to www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-66', 'Cosmic Oilspot', 'Cone 5/6', 'Cosmic Oil Spot is a dark glaze with shimmery flecks that create streams and spots of color similar to a traditional hare’s fur glaze. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-67', 'River Rock', 'Cone 5/6', 'The sandy, dark brown tones of River Rock feather into a beautiful ebony before breaking into a rich amber when applied over texture. Subtle green-grey honeycomb shapes appear underneath the amber breaks when this glossy glaze is applied on vertical surfaces. Due to the powdered nature of the materials involved with the dry-mix dipping buckets of this product, their respective health information and labels differ from the brushing glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-68', 'Golden Honey', 'Cone 5/6', 'Semi-gloss warm yellow, Golden Honey is a translucent glaze like whipped honey. Breaks lighter on texture, a richer color where thick. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-69', 'Cosmic Gold Dust', 'Cone 5/6', 'This glaze is currently available at your local distributor. Find a distributor near you HERE . PC-69 Cosmic Gold Dust is a sparkly gold glaze with subtle specks of reds and browns in the light. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes. Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-70', 'Copper Red', 'Cone 5/6', 'Copper Red is an oxblood red that gives the same results in oxidation as a traditional reduction copper glaze​. Copper Red breaks clear on edges or where thin. Apply 3 coats for best results, do not thin glaze. WARNING: This product can expose you to chemicals including Lithium carbonate, which are known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm. For more information go to www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-71', 'Flambe', 'Cone 5/6', 'Flambé​ is a copper red glaze with tones of purple and blue, that gives the same results in oxidation as a traditional reduction copper glaze. Flambé breaks clear on edges or where thin. Apply 3 coats, do not thin glaze. WARNING: This product can expose you to chemicals including Lithium carbonate, which are known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm. For more information go to www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice', 'PC-72', 'Fire & Ice', 'Cone 5/6', 'PC-72 Fire & Ice is deep red where thick and icy blue where thin. Fire & Ice is a reduction copper red for electric firing with a dramatic icy blue-colored break on texture. Apply three coats for best oxblood red color. Layers well over AMACO Celadons, other Potter''s Choice and Satin Matte glazes.Glaze layering fired results may run if paired with a runny glaze. We recommend testing any layering combination prior to putting it on a full ceramic piece. Shake well before use. For best results, do not thin the glaze and apply 3 brush coats to Cone 04 bisque. (Let the glaze dry between coats.) Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-03', 'Midnight Run', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-3 Midnight Run is a glossy dark blue-gray glaze like a velvety night sky. Breaks dark across textured surfaces. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Good at cone 5, more fluid at cone 6. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-16', 'Aurora Breeze', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-16 Aurora Breeze is a hazy pink glaze with hints of blue and purple and dark speckles. It breaks across textured surfaces, developing a warm blush float when thick. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Good at cone 5, more fluid at cone 6.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-18', 'Honeydew', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-18 Honeydew is a glossy pale green glaze like the melon it''s named for. It breaks across textured surfaces and develops a peachy float when thick. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Good at cone 5, more fluid at cone 6. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-19', 'Cirrus Flow', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-19 Cirrus Flow is a glossy pale blue glaze like a delicate cloud. This glaze breaks across textured surfaces and develops a peachy float when thick. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Good at cone 5, more fluid at cone 6. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-21', 'Ocean Drift', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-21 Ocean Drift is a calming blue color, interspersed with fine, dark speckles that add texture and visual interest. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Good at cone 5, more fluid at cone 6.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-33', 'Mystic Tide', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-33 Mystic Tide is earthy green, highlighted by a subtle, mottled texture that adds depth and complexity to the surface. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-36', 'Rose Mist', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-36 Rose Mist features a soft, blush-pink base, with subtle hints of lavender and white swirls. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-54', 'Flux Blossom', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-54 Flux Blossom is glossy pale pink glaze like a fresh flower. It breaks across textured surfaces and develops a nice peachy float when thick. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Good at cone 5, more fluid at cone 6. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-60', 'Sunbeam', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-60 Sunbeam is a radiant golden-yellow with subtle gradations of amber and honey. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-63', 'Sun Shower', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-63 Sun Shower is a pale yellow interspersed with fine, dark speckles. It breaks across textured surfaces and develops a warm blush float when thick. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-74', 'River Birch', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-74 River Birch is a glossy cream glaze with runny dark specks like the bark of a tree. River Birch breaks across textured surfaces and develops a peachy float when thick. Great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Very fluid at cone 5, more so at cone 6. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Potter''s Choice Flux', 'PCF-75', 'Moss Mist', 'Cone 5/6', 'PCF-75 Moss Mist is a glossy cream and green-mottled glaze that breaks across textured surfaces and develops a peachy float when thick. Moss Mist is great for layering with other glazes as a base or top coat. Beautiful on any color of clay. Very fluid at cone 5, more so at cone 6. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-01', 'Black', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Black is an opaque, buttery black glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance. Add SM-1 to other Satin Matte glazes to create shades of each color.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-02', 'Stone', 'Cone 5/6', 'SM-2 Stone is a dark taupe satin glaze, smooth as a weathered rock. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-03', 'Marble', 'Cone 5/6', 'SM-3 Marble is a pale gray satin glaze, just a whisper of color like the polished marble it''s inspired by. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-10', 'Clear Satin', 'Cone 5/6', 'Clear Satin is a smooth, buttery zinc-free clear glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance. Add SM-10 to other Satin Matte colors to create softer tones. Use 2 coats over underglazes for a more translucent result. Zinc-free. Some underglaze colors may be muted with SM-10 Clear Satin: V-370 Velour Black V-361 Jet Black V-316 Light Pink'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-11', 'White', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte White is an opaque, buttery white glaze accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance. Add SM-11 to other Satin Matte glazes to created tinted colors.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-20', 'Light Blue', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Light Blue is an opaque, buttery robin''s egg blue glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-21', 'Dark Blue', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Dark Blue is an opaque, buttery cobalt glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-24', 'Seafoam', 'Cone 5/6', 'SM-24 Seafoam embodies the serene beauty of the ocean, bringing a sense of calm and sophistication to any pottery creation. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-27', 'Teal', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Teal is an opaque, buttery blue-green glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-29', 'Blue Green', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Blue Green is an opaque, buttery deep teal glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-42', 'Mint', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Mint is an opaque, buttery light green glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-44', 'Chartreuse', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Chartreuse is an opaque, buttery pea-green glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-46', 'Moss', 'Cone 5/6', 'SM-46 Moss is a deep forest green, matte glaze with a hint of olive in the final color. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-51', 'Red', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Red is an opaque, buttery scarlet glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-53', 'Cayenne', 'Cone 5/6', 'SM-53 Cayenne is a spicy and warm red satin glaze with an earthy undertone. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-60', 'Goldenrod', 'Cone 5/6', 'SM-60 Goldenrod is a rich, deep yellow matte glaze like a summer flower. Glaze fire to Cone 5-6. Due to variations in raw materials used during manufacturing, we recommend firing glazed test tiles before using each new batch number of glaze.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-63', 'Yellow', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Yellow is an opaque, buttery gold glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Satin Matte', 'SM-68', 'Orange', 'Cone 5/6', 'Satin Matte Orange is an opaque, buttery orange glaze that accentuates textured ware and boasts a classic art deco appearance.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Shino', 'SH-11', 'Chai Gloss', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Chai Gloss Shino is a glossy, 100% mixable mid-fire glaze that yields wonderfully varied shades of cream, orange, and brown depending on the thickness of application.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Shino', 'SH-12', 'Chai Matte', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Chai Matte Shino is a matte, 100% mixable mid-fire glaze that yields wonderfully varied shades of cream, orange, and brown depending on the thickness of application.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Shino', 'SH-21', 'Acai Gloss', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Acai Gloss Shino is a glossy, 100% mixable mid-fire glaze that yields wonderfully varied shades of blue and brown depending on the thickness of application.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Shino', 'SH-22', 'Acai Matte', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Acai Matte Shino is a matte, 100% mixable mid-fire glaze that yields wonderfully varied shades of blue and brown depending on the thickness of application.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Shino', 'SH-31', 'Cacao Gloss', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Cacao Gloss Shino is a glossy, 100% mixable mid-fire glaze that yields wonderfully varied shades of brown and tan depending on the thickness of application.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Shino', 'SH-32', 'Cacao Matte', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Cacao Matte Shino is a matte, 100% mixable mid-fire glaze that yields wonderfully varied shades of brown and tan depending on the thickness of application.'),
