  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-53', 'Pig Pink', 'Cone 05', 'Pig Pink is a lively, opaque cherry blossom colored glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-54', 'Lilac', 'Cone 05', 'Lilac is a opaque, soft orchid glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-56', 'Scarlet', 'Cone 05', 'Scarlet is a lively, opaque red glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-58', 'Brick Red', 'Cone 05', 'Brick Red is a lively, opaque crimson glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-60', 'Lemon', 'Cone 05', 'Lemon is a lively, opaque yellow glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-62', 'Maize', 'Cone 05', 'Maize is a rich, opaque straw-colored glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-64', 'Carrot', 'Cone 05', 'Carrot is a vivid, opaque red-orange glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette', 'TP-65', 'Pumpkin', 'Cone 05', 'Pumpkin is a vivid, opaque orange-colored glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teachers Palette glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. Also try using using Cotton (TP-11) as a base glaze and, using any of the other Teacher''s Palette colors, brush on colorful designs and patterns reminiscent of majolica ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Texturizer', 'TH-1', 'High Fire Texturizer', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6 / Cone 05', 'TH-1 is a rutile-based glaze changer . When layered with other glazes, it tends to produce a golden matte surface. Apply one thin coat of Texturizer under or over another glaze and fire to cone 5 or higher. TH-1 is LEAD FREE and Non Toxic.'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Texturizer', 'TL-1', 'Low Fire Texturizer', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6 / Cone 05', 'Apply TL-1 Texturizer over any Cone 05 glaze to create different textures. Surface textures vary depending on the type of base glaze (gloss, matte, or textured), broadening the glaze palette tremendously. An even wider variety of effects can be achieved by applying TL-1 between coats of two different Cone 05 glazes. WARNING: This product can expose you to chemicals including Lithium carbonate, which are known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm. For more information go to www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG026', 'Gun Metal Green', 'Cone 6', 'One of ou r most popular and versatile glazes. A very runny, richly varied green that can be unpredictable, sometimes creating both matt and gloss areas on a single pot. Combines beautifully with almost all Coyote Glazes, and explodes with crystals in a slow cool. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG028', 'Blue Purple', 'Cone 6', 'A pale blue with soft lavender tones and beautiful blue crystals. Looks different in each firing and explodes with crystals in a slow cool. Treat with care, it can be runny. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG031', 'Red Gold', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most beautiful and pop ular glazes. Red Gold is a golden cream color with streaks of reddish brown. Depending on the thickness and firing, it can achieve a wide range of colors and finishes, sometimes including blue crystals. It can be very runny. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG034', 'Archies Base', 'Cone 6', 'A runny but beautiful glaze. Pale pink or sometimes cream colored on its own, the Archie''s really shines when combined with other glazes, changing their colors and pulling them into interesting new patterns. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG055', 'Opal', 'Cone 6', 'Possibly our runniest glaze, but also one of our most beautiful. Opal is a brilliant pearlescent blue that varies from translucent where thin to mottled where thick. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG056', 'Eggplant', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most varied and exciting glazes, Eggplant breaks from matt purple to glossy green, and develops intense blue crystals when it cools slowly. It can get runny, especially when extra thick or hot. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG057', 'Rhubarb', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful, but runny, glaze, similar to the Archie''s Base but more reliably pink. Combines well with any Coyote glaze. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG058', 'Ice Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A runny but beautiful pale blue glaze. Icy blue crystals appear frequently in this glaze, especially when it is slow cooled. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG240', 'Frosted Topaz', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG241', 'Magenta Sky', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG242', 'Papaya', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG243', 'Parakeet Yellow', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG027', 'Toshi Brown', 'Cone 6', 'An iron glaze with a light brown to yellow-orange color. Often Toshi Brown will develop surface mottling similar to wood or salt fired glazes, without those special firing processes. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG032', 'Rust Brown', 'Cone 6', 'A light brown glaze with a mottled, satin surface. Less breaking than the Shino glazes but with more variation than the Satins. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG035', 'Copper Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A somewhat runny, translucent glaze that pools in textured areas. Copper blue can serve as a nice base glaze, or sometimes an alternative to clear. Fires red in reduction. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG036', 'Crazed Copper', 'Cone 6', 'Very similar to Copper Blue, but lighter in color and covered in fine crazing on most clays. A somewhat runny, translucent glaze that pools in textured areas. Fires red in reduction. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG037', 'Oasis', 'Cone 6', 'A bright electric blue, with a slight translucency when thin, and a deep mottled look over black. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG040', 'Saturated Iron', 'Cone 6', 'A rich, dark iron glaze. Usually has a smooth, deep brown surface, but can also become reddish, especially when slow cooled. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG120', 'Bronze Temmoku', 'Cone 6', 'A dramatic glaze that emulates the look of a gas-fired temmoku when used on a red clay, but produces a beautiful shimmering bronze on white clays. Also looks great combined with the gloss or satin glazes. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG130', 'Snowy Plum', 'Cone 6', 'A specialized glaze with a carefully balanced formula, creating true reduction copper red in your electric kiln. Snowy Plum uses a chemical that reduces the glaze locally, and must be applied very thick for the reduction to work. Care should be taken to prevent running. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG131', 'Oxblood', 'Cone 6', 'A specialized glaze, Oxblood contains a chemical that causes it to reduce locally, producing a true copper red in your electric kiln without a special firing. Because of the way this glaze works, it needs to be very thick to produce the red color. Thinner spots will be clear or grayish. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG160', 'Ivory Crystal', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful glaze with white and transparent tones, which grows large white and gold crystals when slow cooled. Ivory Crystal is perfect for elegant forms like vases and decorative bottles. Crystals grow best on smooth surfaces. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG161', 'Crystal Celadon', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent soft green with pale crystals. Crystals grow best on smooth, white clay. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG162', 'Crystal Lagoon', 'Cone 6', 'One of the most dramatic glazes available, Crystal Lagoon varies from deep cobalt blue where thick to brown where thin, and grows large blue crystals when slow cooled. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG163', 'Crystal Aurora', 'Cone 6', 'A beautifully creamy and translucent glaze, with tones of purple and large blue crystals. One of the most popular of the Crystalline Slow Cools. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG164', 'Crystal Nebula', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful translucent glaze with pale blue tones and gold colored crystals. Check out Ivory Crystal for a similar look without the blue. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG165', 'Rose Crystal', 'Cone 6', 'A pale translucent orange with large pink crystals. Rose Crystal is both cheerful and elegant. Perfect for decorative ware, especially over white clay. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG170', 'Autumn Spice', 'Cone 6', 'A satiny golden brown with a wonderful feel. Turns less reddish and more golden the slower it is cooled, and combines great with other glazes such as Light Gold. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG171', 'Mars Red Iron', 'Cone 6', 'When fired in a regular cycle, the Mars Red Iron is a deep brownish red, similar to Saturated Iron. The slower it is cooled, the more intense it will beco me. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG172', 'Light Gold', 'Cone 6', 'A variegated glaze with brown, orange, blue, and golden tones. Developed as an alternative to Red Gold for people who have problems using that glaze. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG173', 'Summer Spice', 'Cone 6', 'A creamy brown glaze with reddish tones and touches of orange. Often develops tones of blue, especially when slow cooled. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG174', 'Orion', 'Cone 6', 'The signature and most popular glaze of our Constellation Series, Orion is a beautiful glaze that varies from brown where thin, to bronze, to blue where thickest. When slow cooled, it is shot through with golden crystals. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG175', 'Antares', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, intense blue. One of the most dramatic of the Constellation glazes, Antares will develop starry crystals and shades of bronze as it is cooled more slowly. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG176', 'Andromeda', 'Cone 6', 'An astounding deep blue-green color with tones of brown where thin. Has a flowing look in a regular cool and gold crystals when slow-cooled. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG177', 'Aquila', 'Cone 6', 'A golden brown with occasional purple and blue tones when slow cooled, and a greenish blue with brown tones when not. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG178', 'Gemini', 'Cone 6', 'A brown glaze with blue tones when cooled quickly, and bronze tones when slow cooled. Looks vastly changed on different clays and at different thicknesses. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG179', 'Aries', 'Cone 6', 'A shimmering green that can break brown where thin. Aries changes from glossy to matt when slow cooled, as tiny crystals grow across the surface. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG180', 'Honeydew', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful bright green with a slight satiny finish. Great for indoor and outdoor tile, as well as functional ware. Holds up to nearly anything! Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG181', 'Cool Artichoke', 'Cone 6', 'A stony greyish green with a super hard surface and a cool satin finish. Great for the inside and outside of dishes. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG182', 'Satin White Liner', 'Cone 6', 'Perfect for the insides of dishes, Satin White Liner is specially designed to resist crazing, staining, and everything else. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG183', 'Deep Avocado', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful bright green with a slight satiny finish. Great for indoor and outdoor tile, as well as functional ware. Holds up to nearly anything! Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG184', 'Cornsilk', 'Cone 6', 'A durable and inviting satin yellow. Resistant to staining, crazing and knife marking. Cadmium free. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG185', 'Walnut', 'Cone 6', 'A semi-gloss brown with lovely breaking and a super hard surface. Perfect for both functional and decorative ware. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG186', 'Gloss White Liner', 'Cone 6', 'A super durable glossy white glaze, perfect for porcelain. Gentle enough to let underglaze show through, but hard enough to repel acids and dishwashers. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG187', 'Apricot', 'Cone 6', 'A satiny color with a wonderfully unusual finish, soft to the touch but hard against cutlery marking. Apricot is one of the most popular of our Enduro-Color line, a warm stony pink perfect for dishes or tiles. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG188', 'Sweet Plum', 'Cone 6', 'A lovely glossy purple that sometimes breaks to green where thinnest. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG189', 'Beechnut', 'Cone 6', 'A pale brown with some breaking. Ideal for the inside and outside of dishes, or anything else needing a durable surface. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG190', 'Summer Peach', 'Cone 6', 'A very subtle pink. Looks best on porcelain or other bright white clays. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG191', 'Blue Cornflower', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful powdery blue with a super durable finish. Excellent for a liner or nearly any other use. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG210', 'Ancient Iron', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent brown with mesmerizing rivulets, Ancient Iron can display a dazzling array of colors. Under the right circumstances, amber, coffee, purple and blue tones can show across a surface, and gold crystals can even form in the areas where the glaze cools slowest. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG211', 'Azure Dream', 'Cone 6', 'A deep striking blue that cascades over texture, Azure Dream is the most popular Fantasy glaze with our own students and studio members. Pots covered in this glaze have a way of stopping people in their tracks. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG212', 'Enchanted Sunset', 'Cone 6', 'Varying from soft orange to a mottled pink, Enchanted Sunset is loaded with gorgeous microcrystals. The crystals and colors vary with thickness, creating a surface that draws the eye in deeper the longer you look. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG213', 'Fairy Rose', 'Cone 6', 'A bright pink with delicate mottling, the intensity of Fairy Rose is mostly dependent on its thickness. Perfect for adding a bright accent to your work, Fairy Rose combines beautifully with other glazes. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG214', 'Sorcerer''s Stone', 'Cone 6', 'A mottled charcoal gray that looks excellent on dinnerware, Sorcerer''s Stone is a consistent favorite at the Coyote studio. Depending on the clay it can vary from almost black to light gray, sometimes even breaking blue or brown on texture. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG215', 'Unicorn Horn', 'Cone 6', 'Unicorn Horn is one of the most versatile and surprising glazes we have ever made. Varying from pearlescent white, to mottled ivory, to ancient yellow, this magical glaze is perfect for buff clays with lots of texture. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG216', 'Amethyst', 'Cone 6', 'A stunning multihued purple glaze with warm and cool tones blending into eachother like the last minutes of dusk. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG217', 'Antique Pearl', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG218', 'Dragon''s Eye', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG219', 'Firefly Garden', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG220', 'Hydra Scale', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG221', 'Phoenix Egg', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent brown with mesmerizing rivulets, Phoenix Egg can display a dazzling array of colors. Under the right circumstances, amber, coffee, purple and blue tones can show across a surface, and gold crystals can even form in the areas where the glaze cools slowest. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG098', 'Dusty Rose', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent pink that won''t cover underglaze. Develops a slightly bluish haze where thickest. Great for any application, though colors show best on white clays. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG099', 'Sedona Sunset', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, translucent color that adds warmth to any piece without hiding detail. Easy to apply and reliable. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG100', 'Peach Blush', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent pale pink. A unique and warm alternative to traditional celadon finishes, Peach Blush is perfect for porcelain. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG101', 'Stormy Sea', 'Cone 6', 'A deep gray-green Celadon with deeper green tones and splashes of blue where thickest. Great for any work with texture or underglazes Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG102', 'Aqua', 'Cone 6', 'A gentle, translucent blue-green color, similar to a traditional celadon. Easy to apply and reliable. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG103', 'Key Lime', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent green, great for any piece with texture or underglaze. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG104', 'Peacock Green', 'Cone 6', 'Our best-selling Celadon! A deep translucent green, which pools to a cloudy blue where thickest. Peacock Green is not recommended for food ware, as it can change color when exposed to acids such as lemon or vinegar. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG105', 'Root Beer', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent brown that pools beautifully. Varies from caramel to deep chestnut depending on the thickness. Unlike the other Celadons, Root Beer can be a bit runny. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG106', 'Sunshine Yellow', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, translucent yellow. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG107', 'Night Sky', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent greenish gray, which develops a blue haze where it is thickest. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG108', 'Sapphire', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, clear blue. Translucent enough to be used over fine details or underglaze, Sapphire starts as a pale blue and becomes darker as it pools. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG109', 'Rainy Day', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent bluish purple, pooling to blue where thickest and sometimes breaking gray where thinnest. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG111', 'Iris', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent purple. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG112', 'Jade', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent deep green. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG113', 'Pomegranate', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent vivid red. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG114', 'Sky', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent light blue. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG115', 'Tangerine', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent bright orange. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG116', 'Midnight Rain', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent deep blue. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG001', 'Almost Teal', 'Cone 6', 'A deep blue with a smooth, glossy surface. As easy to use as it is beautiful, Almost Teal is one of the most popular starting points for glaze combinations. Great for beginners and advanced potters alike. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG002', 'Black', 'Cone 6', 'A solid, opaque black with a smooth, glossy finish. Ideal for nearly any usage, on its own or combined with other glazes. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG005', 'Chrome Green', 'Cone 6', 'A solid, unbreaking green. The pigment in Chrome Green will react with Archie''s Base and cause it to flash pink, making this color a great choice for combining with that series. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG006', 'Cinnamon Stick', 'Cone 6', 'A rich glossy brown. Great on its own or combined with the Archie''s series, Cinnamon Stick develops a slight bluish haze at its thickest. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG007', 'Clear', 'Cone 6', 'The perfect cover for underglaze, Coyote Clear Glaze is zinc-free and can be used o ver pinks and reds without damaging them. With proper application and firing, it provides a totally clear glassy surface. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG008', 'Cobalt Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A deep and intense blue that becomes darker as it gets thicker. Great for any use that calls for a darker color. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG011', 'Eggshell', 'Cone 6', 'A stable and reliable glaze that is less bright than White, but has the same glossy finish. Great as a liner glaze for functional ware. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG013', 'Light Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy, translucent blue. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG015', 'Mint', 'Cone 6', 'A light seafoam green. Looks lovely with Shino glazes, or on its own for a bright glossy finish. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG017', 'Red Orange', 'Cone 6', 'A bright red-orange glossy glaze. Doesn''t run and provides a smooth, bold color. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG019', 'Red', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, intense red with less brightness and a more natural tone compared to our Really Red. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG020', 'Orange', 'Cone 6', 'A warm glossy orange. Great on any pot, and combines with any glaze. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG023', 'White', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy, bright white, with a smooth surface. Won''t run, works great on its own or as a base for other glazes. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG025', 'Yellow Orange', 'Cone 6', 'A yellow orange glossy glaze that doesn''t run. Try firing it in a cone 6 soda kiln for a truly transformative look. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG048', 'Oatmeal', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy off-white flecked with dark brown specks. Has a smooth, glossy surface when fired. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG050', 'Buttercup', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, cheerful yellow. Perfect as an accent color, or as a contrasting layer to dark colors like Blue Shino or Espresso Bean. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG051', 'Pumpkin', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy opaque orange with lovely reddish tones. Won''t run, glossy finish. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG053', 'Pansy Purple', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, dark, intense purple color, the "really purple" answer to our Really Red glaze. Provides a solid, unbreaking finish. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG054', 'Violet', 'Cone 6', 'A light but vibrant purple. Perfect for adding warmth to a piece. Potters looking for a more intense purple should look at Pansy Purple, as well. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG071', 'Really Red', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most famous glazes, a true, bright red that won''t quit. Truly eye-catching, and great as an accent or across a whole piece. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG024', 'Blue Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A soft blue that can sometimes be yellowish-brown when thin. Perfect for nearly any non-functional ware, this glaze absorbs light in a striking way and feels warm and dry to the touch. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG029', 'Creamy Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A creamy off-white with a flat finish. Unlike most of the other Matt glazes, Creamy Matt is tough enough to resist scratches from silverware, and so is suitable for functional ware when properly applied and fired. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG030', 'Creamy Matt W/ Specks', 'Cone 6', 'A favorite glaze of potters of all stripes. Creamy with Specks is the same durable off-white color as the original Creamy Matt, but with additional dark specks that add variation to the surface. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG033', 'Turquoise Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A deep turquoise color, rough to the touch. Perfect for small accents, or to add a field to a decorative piece. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG047', 'Green Matt', 'Cone 6', 'One of the most popular glazes in the Matt Series, Green Matt has a nicely variegated surface that breaks from green to black. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG049', 'Iron Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A neutral brown color with limited breaking. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG062', 'Blue Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'An exciting, exotic glaze that sometimes changes from blue to green depending on where it is placed in the kiln. Ideal for adding detail to sculptures, or as an unusual finish for non-functional ware. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG063', 'Cactus Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A muted green that can add a unique look to any decorative ware. Cactus Crawl has an unusual but natural look, making it great for fountains and other outdoor features. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG064', 'Chocolate Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A chocolate brown glaze with a rough, irregular texture, similar to tree bark. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG065', 'Croc Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A dark, scaly green like the skin of a crocodile. Great for sculptures and other decorative uses. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG073', 'White Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'The simplest and most popular of our crawl glazes, White Crawl is great for any decoration that needs a dramatic surface. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG110', 'Black Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A much requested late addition to our Crawl Series, Black Crawl is a charcoal-colored glaze with a unique crackle pattern. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG012', 'Fire Opal', 'Cone 6', 'A bright pink with a lovely haze where thick. Fire Opal is great on its own, and combines well with both the Gloss and Archie'' Series. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG016', 'Mottled Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A base of black that turns a deep and variegated cobalt blue where thick. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG021', 'Sunset Pink', 'Cone 6', 'An intense mottled pink, with a paler pink haze where thick. Provides a smooth and glossy finish with a subtle intensity. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG038', 'Pam''s Green', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most popular glazes, especially when combined with the Archie''s Base. A deep, mottled green with a rich variegated surface. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG066', 'JB''S Brown', 'Cone 6', 'A rich, unbreaking brown. Where thickest, it develops a slight purplish haze. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG070', 'Pam''s Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A mottled greyish blue. Provides the same surface variety as Pam''s Green, but with a less intense color. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG074', 'Alabaster Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A smooth, not quite glossy white, Alabaster Satin is ideal as a liner glaze for functional ware. Try using it with underglaze like a majolica base. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG075', 'Baby Blue Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright blue that feels warm and soft. Doesn''t run, combines great with other colors, especially more mobile ones like the Archie''s Series. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG076', 'Cerulean Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A deep blue that absorbs the light and draws the eye. Cerulean Satin works great on its own, and looks even better under Bronze Temmoku or Archie''s Base. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG077', 'Charcoal Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A great alternative to Black for potters looking for less shine on their finished work. A natural looking dark charcoal color that absorbs light. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG078', 'Cherry Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, true red. Similar to the Really Red glaze, but with a less glossy finish that absorbs the light. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG079', 'Coral Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A pinkish red with a buttery surface. Doesn''t break or run, combines great with other glazes. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG080', 'Forest Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A solid, unbreaking green. Forest Satin looks great on its own, or under other, runnier colors. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG081', 'Hazelnut Satin', 'Cone 6', 'An unbreaking brown, suitable for nearly any use. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG082', 'Lapis Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A deep bluish purple with no breaking. Gun Metal Green and Lapis Satin is one of the most popular combinations of glaze, creating something unlike both colors. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG083', 'Lemon Cream Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright and unbreaking yellow, similar to Buttercup but without the glossy finish. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG084', 'Orchid Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A warm purple, considerably brighter and less blue than the Lapis Satin. Orchid Satin''s bright tones and subtle surface make it a perfect contrast to darker, glossier glazes. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG085', 'Seafoam Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright bluish green with a smooth, buttery feel. Great as a slghtly calmer, less glossy alternative to Mint. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG042', 'Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A deep charcoal color that breaks black over texture. Can be glossy or satiny depending on the thickness and firing environment. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG043', 'Blue Shino', 'Cone 6', 'Dark blue where thick, reddish-brown where thinner. A rich glaze that looks great over texture or combined with other glazes. Contrasts great with bright colors like Buttercup. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG044', 'Green Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A dark green that breaks to brown over texture, and has a metallic sheen where thicker. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG045', 'Light Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A lighter version o f our Shino glaze, Light Shino is a creamy beige where it pools, and breaks to a darker brown over texture. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG059', 'Espresso Bean', 'Cone 6', 'A variegated black and brown color. Popular for combining with brighter colors like any dark Shino, or as a more natural looking alternative to Black. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG061', 'Desert Sage', 'Cone 6', 'Varying from a sagebr ush green to a dark reddish brown, Desert Sage is one of the most popular Shino Glazes. The natural green and brown tones look great on nearly any work. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG067', 'Light Blue Shino', 'Cone 6', 'In its thickest spots, Light Blue Shino is a pale blue, but where thinner it breaks to brown. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG068', 'Light Green Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A pale green that breaks to reddish brown over texture. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG086', 'Butterscotch Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A neutral tone that breaks to dark brown over texture, and produces a marvellous furred pattern over Gloss glazes. A great glaze for adding warmth to textured pieces. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG087', 'Cedar Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A variegated reddish-brown that breaks over texture. Often attains a lacquer-like finish, but can turn glossy pink where thickest. Beatiful with Black. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG088', 'Goldenrod Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A warm yellow glaze that breaks to brown over texture. Breaks less than the other Shino Glazes, but still provides the same signature look. Great to layer with darker colors. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG089', 'Leopard Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A slightly lighter shino dusted with orange-brown spots. Breaks to brown over texture, and combines with other glazes. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG090', 'Mocha Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A b eautiful glaze the color of coffee and cream, which breaks to dark brown where thin. Has a more satiny finish than most of the other Shinos. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG092', 'Plum Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A fairly muted purple that breaks brown over texture. The purple color will be most intense where the glaze is thickest. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG093', 'Pistachio Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A mint green Shino glaze, breaking to brown where thinner. One of our most popular glazes! Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG094', 'Sandstone Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A light brown with some cream tones, breaking darker brown over texture. Has a less glossy finish than most other Shino glazes, usually resulting in a nice satin. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG096', 'Steel Gray Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A warm color with pink and orange tones that breaks to brown where thin. Looks amazing over black! Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG097', 'Sunrise Shino', 'Cone 6', null),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG140', 'Licorice', 'Cone 6', 'A Texas Two-Step undercoat, designed to be used with the overcoats for oilspots. On its own, it is a mottled glossy black. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG141', 'Coffee Bean', 'Cone 6', 'When covered by one of the Texas Two-Step overcoats, Coffee Bean produces the series signature oilspots. When used on its own, it is a darkly mottled brown, with a look similar to leather. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG142', 'Brick Red', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, solid red. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Brick Red is a Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG143', 'Fern', 'Cone 6', 'A bright sea green. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Fern is a Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG144', 'Mulberry', 'Cone 6', 'A deep dark purple. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Mulberry is a Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the six overcoats is laid on top of an undercoat, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG145', 'Persimmon', 'Cone 6', 'A vivid orange. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Persimmon is the brightest Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the six overcoats is laid on top of an undercoat, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG150', 'Blue Moon', 'Cone 6', 'Blue Moon is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, meaning it can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. It is also a beautiful soft blue on its own, making it suited to decorative and functional ware. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG151', 'Birch', 'Cone 6', 'Birch is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, and can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. It can also be used on its own for a slightly mottled, neutral color. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG152', 'Texas Rose', 'Cone 6', 'Texas Rose is a lovely reddish pink, with an interesting mottling to the surface that can only be seen up close. It is also a Texas Two Step Overcoat, which can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG153', 'Marshmallow', 'Cone 6', 'Marshmallow is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, meaning it can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. On its own, it is a glossy off-white, somewhere between Eggshell and Creamy Matt. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG154', 'Sea Mist', 'Cone 6', 'Sea Mist is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, meaning it can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. When used alone, it is a mottled blue-green that can develop pale spots on its own. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG155', 'Clementine', 'Cone 6', 'Clementine is a bright orange that adds a warm pop to any palette. It is also a Texas Two Step Overcoat, which can be layered with one of the six Two Step Undercoats to produce an oilspot effect. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG200', 'Mediterranean Sea', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful glossy blue with a stain resistant finish that looks especially bright on white clays like B-Mix. Perfect for dishes, vases, tiles, and anything else. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG201', 'Passion Red', 'Cone 6', 'A vivid red with a smooth glossy surface. Not only is Passion Red scratch resistant, stain resistant, and craze resistant, it''s also less prone to the pinhole problem that affects many other red glazes. Vibrant, beautiful, and easy to use, it''s quickly becoming a Coyote favorite. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG202', 'Periwinkle', 'Cone 6', 'A pale lavender glaze with a lovely satin finish. Periwinkle should be applied heavily to ensure even coverage, as it can look a bit patchy where thin. When used correctly, it is a beautiful purplish blue ideal for homewares. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG203', 'Sundrop', 'Cone 6', 'Sundrop is a bright and cheery yellow with a hard glossy surface. It resists staining, scratching and crazing, while providing a warm vibrance to any piece. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG204', 'Tiger Lily', 'Cone 6', 'Tiger Lily is a bright and cheery orange with a hard glossy surface. It resists staining, scratching and crazing, while providing a warm vibrance to any piece. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG205', 'Turquoise Lake', 'Cone 6', 'Maybe our most requested glaze, Turquoise Lake has the same color as our popular Turquoise Matt but in a smooth, glossy, and food safe finish! Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.')
on conflict (brand, code) where created_by_user_id is null and code is not null
